I'm sorry folks but pvp should not be the focus of the dev team.  It needs to be &quot;as is&quot; until stability is increased for the world, glaring issues with class bugs and various other PvE issues are addressed first.  If fixing those bugs and working on PvE issues has positive effects on the PvP game then great!  But please realize this game was obviously not designed with pvp in mind.<br />
<br />
If you want to pvp try Eve Online.  It was built from the ground up with pvp in mind.  Granted those who pvp vs those who just want to grief and be general anonymous assholes is rather lop sided (favoring the assholes) but meh, that's what pvp is right?  Rarely is PVP every about actually facing another human player in a battle of skill.  Mostly it's just about ganking someone weaker, ruining someone's fun and being the big bad bully you never had the guts to be in real life.  <br />
<br />
ZZ
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
		<div class="postfoot">
