				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1097918">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							MMO's come in two varieties imo, PVE and PVP based. WoW is heavily PVP based. Always has been, and it's in the very core of the design. Anything with a hardline faction war on a &quot;PVE&quot; server is a pvp based game.<br />
<br />
Vanguard is a PVE based game. You can gain faction with anyone, and you can lose faction with anyone. PVP is just an afterthought because so many people ask for it you simply can't ignore that much of your playerbase. PVP had better not affect our class much. Never really has. If our class had been balanced around pvp we'd do barely half the damage we do now.<br />
<br />
Thankfully, these devs are going to cater toward making a world, not making a FPS with 60 levels.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
