				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1099471">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							They have always stated that the code supports different skill adjustments for different servers and that PVE is the main focus. PVP has always been a part of their plans to my knowledge, just one that would not happen so soon. As in, when they finally were released (this was said back when the devs said that the pvp servers would come after release) they would be on different rulesets.<br />
<br />
This means that<br />
1) PVP servers as they stand today are not balanced for it because they have not made all the changes yet.<br />
2) Changes on PVE servers and PVP servers can happen independently. <br />
<br />
Number 2 is the key factor, and the most important one to me. As I play PVE and could care fuckall about PVP. Always hated in wow when I saw skills &quot;balanced&quot; for PVP that affected me. Hopefully in Vanguard that will not be such a major factor, and nor should it be. They are different servers, and should have different rulesets.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
